    "body": "### Problem\n\nMy Neovim, in the latest version, is causing the delete key to delete twice when pressed. When I go back to version 0.11, it works normally. However, when I switch to version 0.12, the problem persists. This also happens even if I download and run it in isolation. This bug is occurring on the latest version of Ubuntu.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nv0.12\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ntwo delete\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nv0.12\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbunut\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\napt",
